  "text": "ASRock Phantom PG27Q15R2A monitor $138 $210 Save $72 Prime Day is starting to wind down with just one more full day left, but that doesn't mean there aren't plenty of great deals to still take advantage of. Luckily, we're now starting to see other retailers get a bit more competitive with deals of their own, like this awesome budget gaming monitor from ASRock that's now being discounted to $138 for a limited time. Related I've reviewed dozens of gaming monitors. Here's what brands get right (and wrong) Same panels, but some important differences between major gaming monitor brands. What's great about this ASRock gaming monitor? So the big question here is going to be what are you getting for $138? Well, the short answer is that you're getting a feature-packed monitor that's perfect for gamers on a budget. When it comes to the hardware, you're getting a 27-inch panel with a 1500R curve that delivers a 165Hz refresh rate and 1ms response time. The monitor is pretty bright, coming in with 550 nits, and the colors are pretty good as well, with 87% DCI-P3 color coverage. In addition, you also get support for VESA DisplayHDR 400 and AMD FreeSync Premium technologies. You can also protect your eyes during long sessions with ASRock's Low Blue Light feature. When it comes to connectivity, you're getting two HDMI and one DisplayPort. So you can feel free to plug in your PC, along with any other compatible devices like game consoles, streaming sticks, and more. And as an added bonus, the monitor also has integrated Wi-Fi antennas, just in case you want to take your wireless connection even further. The best part is that this monitor isn't all that expensive at its current price of $138. Normally, Newegg's retail price for this product is $210. So you can see that this special discount is pretty steep, which means it won't last for long. It might be for everyone, but you're getting a lot of bang for your buck here. Or if you want some other options, be sure to take a look at these other gaming monitors.",
