or VESA DisplayHDR 400 and AMD FreeSync Premium technologies. You can also protect your eyes during long sessions with ASRock\u0026#39;s Low Blue Light feature. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eWhen it comes to connectivity, you\u0026#39;re getting two HDMI and one DisplayPort. So you can feel free to plug in your PC, along with any other compatible devices like game consoles, streaming sticks, and more. And as an added bonus, the monitor also has integrated Wi-Fi antennas, just in case you want to take your wireless connection even further. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eThe best part is that this monitor isn\u0026#39;t all that expensive at its current price of $138. Normally, Newegg\u0026#39;s retail price for this product is $210. So you can see that this special discount is pretty steep, which means it won\u0026#39;t last for long. It might be for everyone, but you\u0026#39;re getting a lot of bang for your buck here. Or if you want some other options, be sure to take a look at these other \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/best-gaming-monitors/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003egaming monitors\u003c/a\u003e. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                                            \n\n\n\n\n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
